text: Valley Grove is an unincorporated community in Walla Walla County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== Valley Grove had its start around 1881 when the railroad was extended to that point. A post office called Valleygrove was established in 1890, and remained in operation until 1900. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Walla Walla County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Valley Grove, Washington
